    "calculator_page": {
        "schema_version": "1.0",
        "page": {
            "id": "calculator",
            "order": 5,
            "nav_label": "Scoring Calculator",
            "title": "Scoring Calculator",
            "subtitle": "Enter DVH metrics, see your score, and track improvement"
        },
        "sections": [
            {
                "id": "intro",
                "title": "Purpose",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "Use this calculator to turn your plan's DVH metrics into a single, transparent score (out of **150**), using the fixed scorecard for this challenge.",
                    "",
                    "The intent is **education and benchmarking**: practise making defensible trade-offs quickly, then track improvement over repeated attempts."
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "how_it_works",
                "title": "How Scoring Works",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "- Each line item has a **weight** (clinical importance).",
                    "- Your entered value lands in a **bin** (unacceptable → ideal).",
                    "- The calculator converts that bin into points for that metric, then totals everything.",
                    "- Points are assigned by bin position: unacceptable=0%, marginal=25%, acceptable=50%, good=75%, ideal=100% of the metric weight. For 3-bin metrics: 0%, 50%, 100%. For 2-bin metrics: 0%, 100%.",
                    "",
                    "Two metrics are marked as **safety gates** (spinal canal and spinal canal PRV). A high score is meaningless if a safety gate is failed.",
                    "",
                    "Reporting-only metrics (Trachea, Brachial Plexus R PRV) accept a value for your records but do not contribute to the total score."
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "interpretation",
                "title": "Interpreting Your Score",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "- **First pass goal:** everything at least **acceptable**, and **all safety gates passed**.",
                    "- **Next:** improve one metric at a time (high-weight targets, lung dose, oesophagus Dmean) without breaking a gate.",
                    "- **Reality check:** the best plan is not always the highest score; use the score to make your trade-offs visible, not to override clinical judgement."
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "history",
                "title": "Saving Attempts (Personal History)",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "Your saved attempts store **numbers and scores only** (no patient identifiers). Use notes for learning points, not clinical details:",
                    "",
                    "- \"Reduced oesophagus overlap with slight posterior shift; spinal canal PRV improved by 1.2 Gy.\"",
                    "- \"Switched to 2-arc partial; lung V16Gy improved without increasing heart Dmean.\"",
                    "",
                    "Use the **View history** button below to open your saved attempts."
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "disclaimer",
                "title": "Important",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "This tool is for **education/self-audit**. It does not replace local protocols, peer review, physics checks, or clinician decision-making."
                ]
            },
            {
                "id": "reflection_prompts",
                "title": "Reflect on Your Plan",
                "body_markdown_lines": [
                    "After saving your attempt, take a few minutes to consider these questions. They are designed to encourage deliberate practice — not to score you further.",
                    "",
                    "1. **Which trade-off cost you the most points?** Could you have made a different choice that preserved more of the competing metric without breaking a safety gate?",
                    "2. **If you had to re-plan for the same patient tomorrow, what would you change first?** Identify the single highest-impact optimisation step you would try.",
                    "3. **Would you accept this plan for a real patient?** If your answer differs from what the scorecard says, think about what the scorecard does not capture (e.g. deliverability, setup uncertainty, patient preference).",
                    "4. **What surprised you?** Was there a metric that was harder (or easier) to achieve than you expected? What does that tell you about this anatomy or this regimen?"
                ]
            }
        ],
